oai_dc:dc.dc:title: [Temperance Parade, 1907]
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: C.A. Wayland, So. Knoxville, TN
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Hist. Photo Copy Project 2011-012-123 Parade. [Temperance parade, March 1907. Taken at the corner of Main Street and Gay Street, Knoxville, TN]. Destroyed building in background was the Woman's Building which burned December 26, 1906 (streetcar barn later occupied that site). Frank Carpenter, Livery, Board & Sales, Stable signs on building to left of ruins. Sign in crowd: “The Future Is Ours.” #30. Stereo by C.A. Wayland, So. Knoxville, Tenn.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Parades & processions; Temperance; Stereographs;
